at the time of reactor pressure vessel melt-through (destruction) by corium in the formed hole by the action of residual pressure in the reactor pressure vessel, the melt begins to outflow and gases which are released inside the space of the layered vessel and inside the peripheral spaces located between the layered vessel, filler and cantilever truss are vented, gas pressure is quickly increased in these spaces following which the destruction of the corium localizing and cooling system in the welding zone of the layered vessel with the cantilever truss may take place;
